# Example environment variables for the Talos frontend.
# VITE_API_URL points the UI to a GraphQL endpoint. When using the mock
# server included in this repo, set it to http://localhost:4001.
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:4003

# ── Public tunnel (optional, local dev) ──────────────────────────────
# When NGROK_AUTHTOKEN is set, `make up` starts an ngrok sidecar
# (compose profile `public`) that publishes the controller on a public
# https origin, and the controller auto-discovers that origin for every
# externally-reachable URL it formats (GCP Pub/Sub push endpoints,
# Google watch webhooks, inbound webhooks, approval links). Get a token
# at https://dashboard.ngrok.com/get-started/your-authtoken.
#NGROK_AUTHTOKEN=
# Reserved domain (ngrok free tier includes one static domain, e.g.
# example-talos.ngrok-free.app). STRONGLY recommended: without it every
# stack restart mints a new URL and provider-side registrations go
# stale. Claim yours at https://dashboard.ngrok.com/domains.
#NGROK_STATIC_DOMAIN=
# Explicit override — wins over ngrok discovery (production origin or a
# hand-managed tunnel). Scheme + host only, no path.
#TALOS_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=
